Both CI QC failures have been resolved in commit 4e36c76:                   
                                                                              
  1. GO_0004092** (no-label violation)**: The MONDO BOT extraction for        
  MONDO_0011642 (carnitine acetyltransferase deficiency) — newly added in this
  batch — pulled GO_0004092 into the build without a label (MONDO declares it 
  as an empty class). Fixed by adding GO_0004092 to go_import.owl with label  
  "carnitine O-acetyltransferase activity", parent GO_0003824 (catalytic      
  activity), and EC:2.3.1.7 xref. Also added to go_terms.txt files.           
  2. HP_0032373** (dangling violation)**: HP_0032373 (Duffy blood group) had  
  no rdfs:subClassOf in the extracted HP import (its parent HP_0032223 was    
  filtered out during the BOT+filter pipeline). Fixed by adding HP:0032373,   
  HP:0010970 to subclasses.csv, placing it under HP_0010970 (Blood group      
  antigen abnormality), which chains up through HP_0001877 → HP_0001871 →     
  HP_0000118 → EFO_0000651.

